ed as a Dame Commander of the Most Excellent Order of the British Empire by Queen Elizabeth. In 2013 Gordon received an honorary degree from Queen's University in Canada<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.queensu.ca/gazette/content/honorary-degree-recipients-straddle-science-politics|title=Honorary degree recipients straddle science, politics|author=|date=|work=queensu.ca|accessdate=11 March 2016}}</ref>\nIn December 2015 Gordon was honoured at a gala in New York celebrating female empowerment hosted by the Girl Be Heard theatre company. The company praised Gordon, saying \"Dame Pamela Gordon-Banks has broken countless ceilings, educationally and economically. She thinks globally and acts locally\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.royalgazette.com/article/20151203/NEWS/151209870|title=Dame Pamela Gordon-Banks honoured at gala|author=|date=3 December 2015|work=The Royal Gazette|accessdate=11 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Premiers of Bermuda}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gordon, Pamela}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1955 births]]\n[[Category:Bermudian businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Female premiers and first ministers]]\n[[Category:Premiers of Bermuda]]\n[[Category:United Bermuda Party politicians]]\n[[Category:Leaders of the Opposition (Bermuda)]]\n[[Category:20th-century women rulers]]\n[[Category:Women government ministers of Bermuda]]\n", "name_user": "Netoholic", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:clean up, replace DBE link, replaced:DBE\u2192DBE", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pamela_Gordon_(politician)"}
